    },
    {
      '@type': 'Question',
      name: 'How much biotin should I take daily for hair?',
      acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'The Adequate Intake (AI) for biotin established by the National Institutes of Health is 30 micrograms per day for adults. However, most biotin gummies provide 2500 to 5000mcg per serving, which is 8,333 to 16,667 percent of the AI. These higher doses are used in clinical studies examining hair and nail benefits and are considered safe because biotin is a water-soluble vitamin and excess is excreted in urine rather than stored. There is no established Tolerable Upper Intake Level for biotin. Most dermatologists recommend 2500 to 5000mcg daily for individuals specifically targeting hair and nail benefits, with a minimum 3 to 6 month commitment before evaluating results.' },
    },
