    <h2 id="why-biotin">Why Biotin Gummies Are the #1 Beauty Supplement in America</h2>

    <p>Biotin — also known as vitamin B7 or vitamin H (from the German <em>Haar</em> and <em>Haut</em>, meaning hair and skin) — is a water-soluble B-complex vitamin that serves as a coenzyme for five carboxylase enzymes critical to fatty acid synthesis, amino acid metabolism, and keratin infrastructure. Keratin is the structural protein that forms the physical foundation of hair strands, nail plates, and the outer layer of skin, making biotin the single most direct nutritional link between supplementation and visible beauty outcomes.</p>

